StringWithMarkup.String: Thionyl chloride appears as a colorless to yellow fuming liquid with a suffocating pungent odor. Boiling point 79°C. A lachrymator. Highly corrosive and toxic. Long-term inhalation of low concentrations or short-term inhalation of high concentrations has adverse health effects.
COLOURLESS-TO-YELLOW OR REDDISH FUMING LIQUID WITH PUNGENT ODOUR.
Colorless to yellow to reddish liquid with a pungent odor like sulfur dioxide.
Colorless to yellow to reddish liquid with a pungent odor like sulfur dioxide. [Note: Fumes form when exposed to moist air.]
